WEBVTT

00:11.750 --> 00:12.925
Narrator: AT THIS MOMENT,

00:12.969 --> 00:16.364
YOUNG NED IS
9 YEARS, 9 MONTHS, 15 DAYS,

00:16.407 --> 00:18.670
10 HOURS, AND 2 MINUTES OLD.

00:18.714 --> 00:21.934
AWAKENED BY
LONELINESS-INDUCED INSOMNIA,

00:21.978 --> 00:25.460
HE FOUND HIMSELF
IN DESPERATE NEED OF COMFORT.

00:25.503 --> 00:28.680
AND COMFORT FOR NED MEANT PIE.

00:28.724 --> 00:30.334
THE RISKS WERE GREAT,

00:30.378 --> 00:33.946
BUT YOUNG NED RATIONALIZED
HIS ROGUE IMPULSE-BAKING

00:33.990 --> 00:36.514
AS SHEEP-COUNTING.

00:36.558 --> 00:38.951
WHAT HARM COULD COME
OF A SINGLE PIE,

00:38.995 --> 00:42.781
IN THE DARK OF NIGHT, WITH ALL
THE EVIDENCE INGESTED?

00:42.825 --> 00:45.219
HE WAS CAUGHT
IN FLAGRANTE DELICTO

00:45.262 --> 00:47.743
BY ONE EUGENE MULCHANDANI,

00:47.786 --> 00:50.572
WHO IMMEDIATELY JOINED HIM
IN THE ACT.

00:50.615 --> 00:55.490
NED AND EUGENE WERE UNPREPARED
FOR WHAT HAPPENED NEXT.

00:55.533 --> 00:58.058
THE AROMA OF FRESHLY BAKED PIE

00:58.101 --> 01:00.103
WAFTING THROUGH
BOARDING-SCHOOL HALLS

01:00.147 --> 01:05.282
AWAKENED AN ENTIRE CLASS WHO
HAD BUT ONE THING IN COMMON --

01:05.326 --> 01:09.721
THEY WERE ALL FAR FROM HOME
AND NEEDED COMFORT.

01:09.765 --> 01:11.375
THE LONGING AND HOMESICKNESS

01:11.419 --> 01:14.204
WHICH FILLED THE SCHOOL
LIKE A PLAGUE

01:14.248 --> 01:16.902
WAS MAGICALLY LIFTED
WITH EVERY BITE.

01:16.946 --> 01:18.121
AND THE PARTY BEGAN.

01:18.165 --> 01:20.254
[ SWING MUSIC PLAYS ]

01:38.185 --> 01:40.100
[ MUSIC STOPS ]

01:40.143 --> 01:43.364
UNTIL THE PARTY STOPPED,

01:43.407 --> 01:44.930
AND YOUNG NED LEARNED

01:44.974 --> 01:47.324
THAT EVEN A FORKFUL
OF IMMEDIATE GRATIFICATION

01:47.368 --> 01:52.155
CAN LEAD TO A WORLD
OF GRAVE CONSEQUENCES --

01:52.199 --> 01:55.158
A LESSON TO BE LEARNED AGAIN
YEARS LATER

01:55.202 --> 01:57.465
AT THE GRAVE OF
CURRENTLY DEAD FATHER

01:57.508 --> 01:59.902
OF CHUCK, THE WOMAN HE LOVED.

02:02.296 --> 02:04.167
[ LID CREAKS ]

02:04.211 --> 02:06.778
READY?

02:06.822 --> 02:09.172
I'M READY, I THINK.

02:09.216 --> 02:10.782
WAIT.
WHAT?

02:10.826 --> 02:12.567
IF WE BOTH HAVE HALF A MINUTE,
THEN YOU GO FIRST.

02:12.610 --> 02:14.177
NO, NO, YOU GO FIRST.

02:14.221 --> 02:15.787
IF YOU SPILL OVER THE FIRST
30 SECONDS, THEN NO BIGGIE.

02:15.831 --> 02:17.572
AS OPPOSED TO SPILLING OVER
THE SECOND 30 SECONDS,

02:17.615 --> 02:19.008
WHICH IS YES BIGGIE.

02:19.051 --> 02:21.706
I BUDGETED EVERY SECOND.
I WON'T SPILL.

02:21.750 --> 02:23.404
THAT'S NOT ENOUGH SECONDS.
YOU SHOULD HAVE ALL 60.

02:23.447 --> 02:24.535
WE DON'T NEED
TO FACT-FIND ABOUT DWIGHT.

02:24.579 --> 02:26.189
I DON'T KNOW
WHAT I WAS THINKING.

02:26.233 --> 02:27.756
YOU WERE THINKING THAT
YOU WERE TRYING TO PROTECT US

02:27.799 --> 02:31.020
FROM A MYSTERIOUS,
POTENTIALLY DANGEROUS MAN.

02:31.063 --> 02:32.195
YOU GO FIRST.

02:32.239 --> 02:34.284
NO, YOU GO.
THIS IS AWKWARD.

02:34.328 --> 02:36.243
GO FIRST, OR I'M GONNA HIT YOU
WITH THE SHOVEL.

02:36.286 --> 02:37.940
[ Sighing ] OKAY.

02:40.551 --> 02:42.074
HELLO.

02:42.118 --> 02:43.380
HI, MR. CHARLES.
OR SHOULD I CALL YOU CHARLES?

02:43.424 --> 02:45.034
IT DOESN'T MATTER.
IT'S ME -- NED.

02:45.077 --> 02:47.819
I LIVED ACROSS THE STREET
WHEN I WAS A LITTLE BOY.

02:47.863 --> 02:49.169
HI.
IT'S ME -- CHARLOTTE.

02:49.212 --> 02:50.431
UM, YOU'VE BEEN DEAD
FOR 20 YEARS.

02:50.474 --> 02:51.954
I'M SURE YOU HAVE
A LOT OF QUESTIONS.

02:51.997 --> 02:53.738
CAN YOU PUT THEM ON HOLD
FOR JUST A SECOND

02:53.782 --> 02:56.263
AND TELL US -- IS DWIGHT DIXON
A DANGEROUS MAN?

02:56.306 --> 02:57.568
OH, YEAH.

02:57.612 --> 02:59.396
OH. OH, NO.
HE STOLE CHUCK'S --

02:59.440 --> 03:01.920
I STILL CALL YOUR DAUGHTER
"CHUCK", LIKE WHEN I WAS 9.

03:01.964 --> 03:02.921
15.

03:02.965 --> 03:04.227
NO, I WAS 9.
SECONDS.

03:04.271 --> 03:06.142
UH, DWIGHT STOLE
YOUR POCKET WATCH

03:06.186 --> 03:07.926
AND LEFT A VEILED THREAT ABOUT
EXPOSING A VERY BIG SECRET

03:07.970 --> 03:10.146
WHICH HE KNOWS THAT WE
PROBABLY DON'T WANT EXPOSED.

03:10.190 --> 03:12.931
OH, IF HE'S GOT THE WATCH,
YOU GOT NOTHING
TO WORRY ABOUT.

03:12.975 --> 03:14.672
THE THREAT'S
HIS INSURANCE POLICY.

03:14.716 --> 03:18.110
NOW, YOU DON'T SAY NOTHING,
HE'LL RETURN THE FAVOR.

03:18.154 --> 03:19.199
GOOD TO KNOW.

03:19.242 --> 03:20.417
YOU'RE UP.

03:20.461 --> 03:22.289
Narrator:
THE PIE MAKER'S GIFT OF LIFE

03:22.332 --> 03:24.987
LASTED
FOR ONE PRECIOUS MINUTE ONLY,

03:25.030 --> 03:28.686
A MINUTE HE EAGERLY SHARED
WITH THE CHUCK OF HIS LIFE,

03:28.730 --> 03:30.558
TO GIVE HER BUT HALF A MINUTE

03:30.601 --> 03:34.692
TO CATCH UP ON A LIFETIME
WITH A FATHER LONG LOST.

03:34.736 --> 03:37.391
30 SECONDS
WERE ALL HE COULD GIVE,

03:37.434 --> 03:39.480
AND NOT A SECOND MORE.

03:39.523 --> 03:40.698
[ THUNDER CRASHES ]

03:46.182 --> 03:47.792
Ned?

03:47.836 --> 03:50.273
Ned.

03:50.317 --> 03:51.622
Are you awake?

03:51.666 --> 03:53.537
Narrator:
AS CHUCK SOUNDLESSLY BROKE

03:53.581 --> 03:55.800
THE BONDS
OF HER PLASTIC-WRAP EMBRACE

03:55.844 --> 03:58.760
AND SNUCK AWAY
TO SEE TO BUSINESS UNATTENDED,

03:58.803 --> 04:02.459
VIVIAN WAITED FOR DWIGHT
DIXON, GENTLEMAN CALLER,

04:02.503 --> 04:05.114
UNAWARE HER SISTER LILY CHASED
HIM OFF THEIR FRONT PORCH

04:05.157 --> 04:07.029
HOURS EARLIER.

04:07.072 --> 04:11.729
AT THE COME AND SLEEP HOTEL,
SISTER LILY WOULD MAKE CERTAIN

04:11.773 --> 04:16.038
DWIGHT DIXON, GENTLEMAN
CALLER, WOULD NEVER CALL
AGAIN.

04:18.432 --> 04:20.738
[ FOOTSTEPS, KEYS JINGLE ]

04:27.963 --> 04:29.660
[ SHOTGUN COCKS ]

04:29.704 --> 04:33.098
WAY I SEE THIS, WE BOTH GOT
SOMETHING YOU WANT.

04:33.142 --> 04:37.059
WHAT WOULD THAT BE,
MY SPICY COCKTAIL?

04:37.102 --> 04:39.235
I GOT
MY DAUGHTER'S WATCH

04:39.279 --> 04:41.629
AND YOU GOT YOUR INSIDES
WHERE YOU WANT 'EM.

04:41.672 --> 04:43.631
YOU'RE GONNA DIG UP
CHARLOTTE'S GRAVE

04:43.674 --> 04:45.807
YOU'RE GONNA PUT THIS WATCH
BACK WHERE YOU FOUND IT --

04:45.850 --> 04:48.853
AFTER YOU TELL ME
YOUR REAL STORY.

04:50.594 --> 04:51.726
WELL.

04:51.769 --> 04:53.945
IT ALL BEGAN
WHEN I WAS CONCEIVED

04:53.989 --> 04:57.166
IN THE SWEAT AND SAWDUST
OF A TRAVELING CARNIVAL.

04:57.209 --> 04:59.255
MY MOTHER
WAS AN ACROBAT NAMED --

05:19.275 --> 05:23.192
Narrator:
AND CHUCK SEEMED TO BE WAITING
FOR SOMETHING ELSE ALTOGETHER.

05:23.235 --> 05:25.281
I'M DECLARING IT
AN EMOTIONAL SNOW DAY.

05:25.325 --> 05:27.631
HUH? BUT YOU LOVE
THAT COOK-OFF.

05:27.675 --> 05:29.459
AND YOU AND OLIVE
DIDN'T GET TO GO LAST YEAR.

05:29.503 --> 05:31.766
I CHOSE NOT TO GO LAST YEAR.
I WAS BUSY.

05:31.809 --> 05:33.115
YEAH, B-BECAUSE OF ME.

05:33.158 --> 05:34.595
I LOVE BEING BUSY
BECAUSE OF YOU,

05:34.638 --> 05:36.205
AND I'M LOOKING FORWARD
TO BEING BUSY BECAUSE OF YOU

05:36.248 --> 05:38.033
FOR THE REST OF THE DAY.

05:38.076 --> 05:39.643
YOU CAN'T DO
WHAT YOU DID LAST NIGHT

05:39.687 --> 05:41.863
AND NOT BE A LITTLE...
OVERWHELMED.

05:41.906 --> 05:43.952
WELL, BELIEVE ME,
I FEEL PLENTY WHELMED,

05:43.995 --> 05:45.736
BUT, UM, NOT OVERLY.

05:45.780 --> 05:47.172
OVERLY IS ON ITS WAY,

05:47.216 --> 05:49.087
PROBABLY LOOKING
IN THE WINDOW RIGHT NOW.

05:49.131 --> 05:51.612
YOU HAD TO SAY "HELLO, AGAIN"
AND "GOODBYE, AGAIN" TO YOUR
DAD

05:51.655 --> 05:52.961
IN 30 SECONDS.

05:53.004 --> 05:54.571
I GUESS
I JUST CHOSE TO LOOK AT IT

05:54.615 --> 05:56.965
LIKE IT WAS 30 MORE SECONDS
THAN I WAS SUPPOSED TO HAVE.

05:58.619 --> 05:59.881
HOW DID THAT GO?

05:59.924 --> 06:01.578
IT WAS STILL HARD,

06:01.622 --> 06:03.624
NO MATTER HOW MUCH
I BUDGETED MY SECONDS.

06:03.667 --> 06:05.669
THE HELLO-AGAINing
WAS WONDERFUL,

06:05.713 --> 06:07.584
AND...THE GOODBYE-AGAINing
WASN'T.

06:10.021 --> 06:12.154
OH, NED, LOOK...

06:12.197 --> 06:13.851
YOU SHOULD JUST GO
TO THE COOK-OFF.

06:13.895 --> 06:15.331
YOU'RE TRYING
TO GET RID OF ME.

06:15.375 --> 06:17.681
NO, I'M NOT TRYING
TO GET RID OF YOU. I JUST...

06:17.725 --> 06:20.684
MAYBE I NEED
AN EMOTIONAL SNOW DAY, TOO.

06:20.728 --> 06:22.860
YOU NEED AN EMOTIONAL SNOW DAY
FROM ME? IS THIS WEIRD NOW?

06:22.904 --> 06:25.950
ARE WE WEIRD NOW BECAUSE
I DID "IT" WITH YOUR DAD?

06:25.994 --> 06:27.343
NO, WE'RE NOT WEIRD.

06:27.387 --> 06:29.432
I'VE NEVER BEEN
SO IN LOVE WITH YOU.

06:29.476 --> 06:32.043
BUT I'M ALSO FEELING
A LOT OF OTHER THINGS --

06:32.087 --> 06:34.437
SO MANY THINGS THAT I WANT TO
TELL YOU AND I CAN'T TELL YOU

06:34.481 --> 06:36.439
AND I'M AFRAID TO TELL YOU AND
I DON'T KNOW HOW TO TELL YOU.

06:36.483 --> 06:38.006
YOU DON'T HAVE TO TELL ME
IF YOU DON'T WANT TO.

06:38.049 --> 06:40.487
I MEAN...
YOU DO EVENTUALLY.

06:40.530 --> 06:42.706
AND I WILL TONIGHT.
I PROMISE.

06:42.750 --> 06:45.056
FOR THE MEANTIME,
OLIVE IS DEPENDING ON YOU.

06:45.100 --> 06:46.928
SHE SAID
TWO YEARS AGO,

06:46.971 --> 06:49.278
SHE COULD TASTE
THAT FIRST-PRIZE BLUE RIBBON,

06:49.321 --> 06:51.802
AND THEN THAT TASTE WAS
REPLACED WITH THE BITTER
TANG OF DEFEAT.

06:51.846 --> 06:54.588
BITTER TANG, BITTER OLIVE.
IT'S A STORY.

06:54.631 --> 06:58.113
AND TODAY IT'S GONNA BE
A HAPPY ENDING.

06:58.156 --> 07:00.115
COME ON.
GO TO THE COOK-OFF.

07:00.158 --> 07:01.421
OLIVE WILL LOVE YOU
FOR IT.

07:06.034 --> 07:07.949
ISN'T IT GOOD
TO BE BACK AGAIN?

07:07.992 --> 07:09.298
JUST YOU AND ME,

07:09.341 --> 07:11.126
SHOULDER-TO-SHOULDER,
EYE-TO-EYE.

07:11.169 --> 07:13.911
DECORATIVE HATS FIXED
SQUARELY ON SWEATY BROWS,

07:13.955 --> 07:16.261
BONDING IN THE FIERY KILN
OF COMPETITION

07:16.305 --> 07:18.002
THAT FORGES MEN'S SOULS.

07:18.046 --> 07:19.439
WE'RE BAKING PIE, OLIVE.

07:19.482 --> 07:22.006
NOT JUST PIE --
DAMN GREAT PIE.

07:22.050 --> 07:23.747
THIS IS OUR YEAR.

07:23.791 --> 07:25.836
WE'RE IN SUCH A BETTER PLACE
THAN WE WERE TWO YEARS AGO.

07:25.880 --> 07:27.795
I, FOR ONE,
AM NO LONGER ENCUMBERED

07:27.838 --> 07:30.058
OF THE TENSION
OF A SEXUAL NATURE TOWARD YOU.

07:30.101 --> 07:32.321
I'M FOCUSED.
WE SHOULD HAVE WON LAST TIME.

07:32.364 --> 07:36.151
WOULD HAVE WON...
HAD WE NOT GOTTEN SCREWED
BY...

07:36.194 --> 07:37.674
THE BUFFALO.

07:37.718 --> 07:41.939
SWEET LORD IN HEAVEN,
HOW I HATE THE BUFFALO.

07:41.983 --> 07:43.637
WHEN YOU SAY "BUFFALO,"

07:43.680 --> 07:45.290
DO YOU MEAN
THE NOBLE BREED OF BISON

07:45.334 --> 07:46.901
LOST FOREVER
TO SETTLERS' GREED

07:46.944 --> 07:48.337
OR THE UPSTATE NEW YORK
HAMLET

07:48.380 --> 07:50.774
STILL THIRSTING
FOR SUPER BOWL GLORY?

07:50.818 --> 07:53.864
I MEAN THAT BIG PHONY
WHIPPING UP THOSE
CRAP MUFFINS OVER THERE.

07:53.908 --> 07:56.476
MARIANNE MARIE BEETLE.
THEY CALL HER THE PASTRY
SLAYER.

07:56.519 --> 07:58.260
[ SCOFFS ]

07:58.303 --> 08:00.349
LEO BURNS, THE NEW COMFORT
FOOD COOK-OFF COORDINATOR,

08:00.392 --> 08:02.133
LOVER
OF ALL THINGS FOODY.

08:02.177 --> 08:04.658
OH, AND I JUST LOVE
THAT ALL FOODS ARE WELCOME

08:04.701 --> 08:06.616
AT THIS YEAR'S
COMFORT FOOD COOK-OFF.

08:06.660 --> 08:08.836
IT'S LIKE BEST IN SHOW,
ONLY "BEST IN BELLY."

08:08.879 --> 08:10.446
[ CHUCKLES ]

08:10.490 --> 08:12.361
WHICH MEANS BUFFALO MUFFIN
WILL BE LOCKING THOSE HORNS

08:12.404 --> 08:13.884
WITH COLONEL LIKKIN.

08:13.928 --> 08:16.365
HE AND THE BUFFALO
ARE THE TEAMS TO BEAT.

08:16.408 --> 08:17.671
THE COLONEL'S BEEN
"BEST IN BELLY"

08:17.714 --> 08:19.542
BLUE-RIBBON WINNER
15 YEARS RUNNING.

08:19.586 --> 08:22.545
BUT THERE'S AN EMPTY WINNER'S
PLATE WAITING TO BE LOADED.

08:22.589 --> 08:25.113
WITH DAMN GREAT PIE.

08:25.156 --> 08:27.594
OH! WELL,
YOU'RE THE PIE HOLERS!

08:27.637 --> 08:30.335
I'M A VERY, VERY,
VERY BIG FAN.

08:30.379 --> 08:31.772
STOP.

08:31.815 --> 08:34.557
AS EVENT COORDINATOR,
I'M NOT ALLOWED TO SAY THIS,

08:34.601 --> 08:35.950
BUT I'M ROOTING FOR YOU.

08:35.993 --> 08:38.082
OH, THANK YOU.

08:38.126 --> 08:40.998
AW, HE'S A DREAMBOAT.

08:41.042 --> 08:42.304
WELL, TUGBOAT,
BUT STILL.

08:42.347 --> 08:43.392
LET'S SET UP, PARTNER.

08:44.611 --> 08:45.960
TED!

08:46.003 --> 08:47.701
IT'S SO NICE TO SEE
THAT YOU CAME BACK

08:47.744 --> 08:49.920
AFTER TAKING A YEAR OFF
TO LICK YOUR WOUNDS

08:49.964 --> 08:52.793
AND HIDE IN THE DANK SHADOWS
OF HUMILIATING DEFEAT.

08:52.836 --> 08:54.272
AND YOU WERE SO CLOSE.

08:54.316 --> 08:56.057
YEAH, MYSTERIOUS.

08:56.100 --> 08:57.624
IT'S AS IF SOMEONE
DELIBERATELY SABOTAGED
OUR OVEN,

08:57.667 --> 08:59.190
CHEATER McGEE.

08:59.234 --> 09:01.758
IT'S A POOR WORKMAN
WHO BLAMES HIS TOOLS.

09:01.802 --> 09:03.673
JUST KEEP YOUR OVEN MITTS
TO YOURSELF.

09:03.717 --> 09:05.762
I INTEND TO, AS I PRESENT

09:05.806 --> 09:08.591
MORE AWARD-WINNING MUFFINS
TO THE JUDGES.

09:08.635 --> 09:10.027
AND YOU REMEMBER, NOW --

09:10.071 --> 09:12.769
LOSING DOESN'T MAKE YOU A LOSER.

09:12.813 --> 09:14.641
OH, WAIT -- IT DOES.

09:14.684 --> 09:16.991
BETTER GET STUFFING
YOUR PIEHOLES.

09:17.034 --> 09:20.168
Narrator:
BUT DESPITE THE FRESHLY STOKED
HEAT OF THE COMPETITION...

09:20.211 --> 09:21.865
THAT BUFFALO
IS GOING DOWN!

09:21.909 --> 09:24.302
...THE PIE MAKER'S THOUGHTS
STRAYED AWAY

09:24.346 --> 09:26.696
FROM PASTRIES TO BE MADE

09:26.740 --> 09:29.003
AND TOWARD CHUCK...

09:29.046 --> 09:32.484
WONDERING WHAT SHE COULD
POSSIBLY BE AFRAID
TO TELL HIM.

09:33.485 --> 09:34.835
HI, DAD.

09:39.100 --> 09:40.928
Narrator:
THE SECRET CHUCK WAS KEEPING
FROM THE PIE MAKER

09:40.971 --> 09:43.191
WAS BORN THE NIGHT BEFORE.

09:43.234 --> 09:45.323
HELLO, AGAIN.

09:45.367 --> 09:48.065
I KNOW I DON'T LOOK
LIKE THE CHARLOTTE THAT
YOU REMEMBER, BUT --

09:48.109 --> 09:49.850
OH, YOU'RE THE CHARLOTTE
I REMEMBER, ALL RIGHT.

09:49.893 --> 09:52.983
[ CHUCKLES ] BUTTON-BUTTON.
CUTE AS A BUTTON.

09:53.027 --> 09:54.898
I MISS YOU, DADDY.

09:54.942 --> 09:57.031
ISN'T THIS NICE?
YES.

09:57.074 --> 10:00.556
SON OF A BITCH. NOW I'M EATING
INTO MY "I LOVE YOU" TIME.

10:00.600 --> 10:05.039
UM, LOOK, I...
I LOVE YOU, AND, UM...

10:06.823 --> 10:08.216
HAPPY BIRTHDAY.

10:08.259 --> 10:10.958
OH, IT'S --
IT'S MY BIRTHDAY?

10:11.001 --> 10:12.699
NOT TODAY,
BUT IT WAS GONNA BE.

10:12.742 --> 10:13.961
THEN I DIED.

10:14.004 --> 10:15.223
YEAH.

10:15.266 --> 10:16.572
I NEVER GOT A CHANCE
TO GIVE IT TO YOU,

10:16.616 --> 10:18.095
BUT NOW I CAN.

10:18.139 --> 10:20.402
SO I GUESS
IT KIND OF IS YOUR BIRTHDAY.

10:20.445 --> 10:24.624
Narrator:
AT THAT VERY MOMENT, A CHANGE
OF PLAN OCCURRED TO HER.

10:24.667 --> 10:26.756
TORN BETWEEN
THE PIE MAKER SHE LOVED

10:26.800 --> 10:29.498
AND THE FATHER SHE LOST,
CHUCK ACTED ON IMPULSE.

10:29.541 --> 10:33.023
You're gonna put on
my glove.

10:33.067 --> 10:35.591
When Ned touches you,
you play dead.

10:35.635 --> 10:38.812
Narrator: THE PIE MAKER GAVE
EVERY SECOND HE COULD GIVE...

10:38.855 --> 10:40.770
I'm gonna be back
to dig you up in an hour.

10:40.814 --> 10:43.338
Narrator:
...AND NOT A SECOND MORE.

10:43.381 --> 10:45.906
[ THUNDER CRASHES ]

10:45.949 --> 10:49.126
[ THUNDER CRASHES ]

10:49.170 --> 10:50.475
YOU OKAY?

10:50.519 --> 10:51.651
UH-HUH.

10:54.871 --> 10:58.875
IT DIDN'T FEEL LIKE 20 YEARS.
[ CHUCKLES ]

10:58.919 --> 11:01.617
WHAT DID IT FEEL LIKE IF IT
DIDN'T FEEL LIKE 20 YEARS?

11:01.661 --> 11:03.053
GLIDING.

11:03.097 --> 11:07.101
HOLDING YOUR BREATH
AND...BEING ABLE TO BREATHE

11:07.144 --> 11:10.147
AND JUST...GLIDING.

11:10.191 --> 11:12.454
I DIDN'T GLIDE.

11:12.497 --> 11:14.412
WHAT BUSINESS
WOULD YOU HAVE GLIDING?

11:14.456 --> 11:15.718
I DIED.

11:15.762 --> 11:18.503
AND THEN NED...
NED TOUCHED ME.

11:18.547 --> 11:22.116
BUT THERE WAS NO GLIDING --
JUST NED.

11:22.159 --> 11:23.552
HE NEVER TOUCHED YOU
AGAIN?

11:23.595 --> 11:25.772
NO, HE CAN'T --
NOT WITHOUT --

11:25.815 --> 11:28.035
GOOD.

11:28.078 --> 11:29.514
HOW IS THIS
EVEN POSSIBLE?

11:29.558 --> 11:30.777
HMM?

11:30.820 --> 11:33.214
YOU, ME, HERE AGAIN
IN THE HERE-AND-NOW

11:33.257 --> 11:35.520
WHEN WE BELONG
IN THE HEREAFTER?

11:35.564 --> 11:37.174
SINCE WHEN DID DEATH
GET A LOOPHOLE?

11:37.218 --> 11:38.654
SINCE NED.

11:38.698 --> 11:41.439
YOUR DREAMS,
THEY'RE GONNA BE SO VIVID NOW.

11:41.483 --> 11:43.398
[ SIGHS ]
IT'S SO NEAT.

11:43.441 --> 11:44.486
AND MY BEES --

11:44.529 --> 11:45.574
YOU HAVE BEES?

11:45.617 --> 11:46.880
SINCE YOU DIED.

11:46.923 --> 11:49.012
AND THEN THEY DIED,
AND THEN...

11:49.056 --> 11:51.580
NED TOUCHED THEM, TOO.

11:51.623 --> 11:53.016
OH, GOD,
AND THEIR HONEY --

11:53.060 --> 11:55.105
YOU HAVE NEVER TASTED HONEY
LIKE THIS BEFORE.

11:55.149 --> 11:57.020
[ CHUCKLES ]

11:57.064 --> 11:58.892
I HATE TO LOOK
IN THE GIFT HORSE'S MOUTH,

11:58.935 --> 12:00.763
BUT I'M NOT GONNA START
CRAVING HUMAN FLESH, AM I?

12:00.807 --> 12:02.460
NO.

12:02.504 --> 12:04.245
ALTHOUGH EVERYTHING
DOES TASTE BETTER.

12:04.288 --> 12:07.509
HMM. WHAT'S THE CATCH,
BUTTON?

12:07.552 --> 12:10.512
HIDING ME AWAY LIKE EVERY
STRAY CAT, DOG, AND GOOSE

12:10.555 --> 12:12.470
THAT MET
YOUR ACQUAINTANCE.

12:12.514 --> 12:13.950
YOU DON'T WANT
NEDLY-DEADLY

12:13.994 --> 12:16.213
TO KNOW THAT
MY BUCKET'S STILL KICKING.

12:16.257 --> 12:18.259
WHY?

12:18.302 --> 12:19.608
IS THERE A CATCH?

12:19.651 --> 12:20.696
NOT THAT
YOU'RE AWARE OF.

12:20.740 --> 12:21.871
WHAT?

12:21.915 --> 12:23.612
NOT THAT I'M AWARE OF.

12:23.655 --> 12:24.831
UM...

12:24.874 --> 12:26.876
THERE'S A CATCH.

12:26.920 --> 12:29.313
AND I'M GONNA CATCH IT
BEFORE I GET CAUGHT.

12:29.357 --> 12:32.882
YOU GONNA TELL ME
WHAT THAT CATCH IS, BUTTON?

12:32.926 --> 12:35.450
I WILL TONIGHT.
I PROMISE.

12:35.493 --> 12:37.887
Narrator: AS CHUCK'S PLAN
WAS PERCOLATING,

12:37.931 --> 12:42.065
PRIVATE INVESTIGATOR
EMERSON COD GENTLY EXTRACTED

12:42.109 --> 12:45.677
THE DELICATE FLAVORS
OF BOLIVIA WARA COFFEE GROUNDS

12:45.721 --> 12:48.550
FOR A SMOOTH, CLEAN
COFFEE EXPERIENCE

12:48.593 --> 12:51.248
ON A MORNING THAT
WOULD SOON PROVE TO BE

12:51.292 --> 12:53.729
ANYTHING BUT SMOOTH OR CLEAN.

12:54.512 --> 12:55.513
EMERSON, I --

12:55.557 --> 12:57.341
[ SLURPING ]

12:59.561 --> 13:02.085
[ EXHALES HEAVILY ]

13:02.129 --> 13:03.565
I NEED YOUR HELP.

13:03.608 --> 13:05.872
FRIEND HELP
OR PAY HELP?

13:05.915 --> 13:09.136
SEE THAT? THAT'S THE KIND
OF BODY LANGUAGE YOU NEVER
HEAR WITH PAY HELP.

13:09.179 --> 13:11.225
NED BROUGHT MY DAD BACK TO
LIFE, BUT ONLY FOR A MINUTE,

13:11.268 --> 13:13.618
AND WHEN THE MINUTE WAS
UP, WE RETOUCHED HIM,
AS WE ALWAYS DO.

13:13.662 --> 13:14.924
NO BIGGIE, BUT YES BIGGIE,

13:14.968 --> 13:16.491
BECAUSE
IN THE HEAT OF THE MOMENT,

13:16.534 --> 13:18.667
MY THINKING WASN'T SO MUCH
AS "THINKING" BUT "FEELING."

13:18.710 --> 13:20.408
AND I TRICKED NED
WITH MY GLOVE,

13:20.451 --> 13:21.975
AND NOW
MY DAD'S STILL ALIVE,

13:22.018 --> 13:24.978
AND NED DOESN'T KNOW,
AND...

13:25.021 --> 13:26.544
PLEASE HELP ME.

13:26.588 --> 13:27.981
WHAT'S THE PART
ABOUT YOUR GLOVES, AGAIN?

13:28.024 --> 13:29.852
I'VE USED NED.

13:29.896 --> 13:32.550
NOW MY DAD'S ALIVE BECAUSE
OF MY IMPULSE-CONTROL ISSUES,

13:32.594 --> 13:35.336
AND...NOW SOMEBODY ELSE
IS DEAD.

13:35.379 --> 13:37.164
FIRST OF ALL, BLOW.

13:38.165 --> 13:39.122
[ BLOWS NOSE ]

13:39.166 --> 13:42.343
SECOND...JUST RELAX.

13:42.386 --> 13:43.735
YOU'RE NOT MAD AT ME?

13:43.779 --> 13:44.780
HELL YEAH, I'M MAD!

13:44.824 --> 13:46.434
I'M STEAMED, FURIOUS, RED-HOT!

13:46.477 --> 13:50.090
AND DON'T THINK I AIN'T
GONNA YELL AT YOU LATER!

13:50.133 --> 13:53.702
BUT FOR NOW, WE SHOULD
JUST PUT OUR HEADS TOGETHER

13:53.745 --> 13:56.052
AND TRY TO FIGURE OUT
WHAT TO DO.

13:58.011 --> 13:59.316
[ GRUMBLES ]

14:01.492 --> 14:03.016
OH, YOU'RE SLOWING
THE ROLL, CHIEF.

14:03.059 --> 14:04.887
I'M IN THE ZONE.

14:04.931 --> 14:07.324
WORKING AWFUL HARD
FOR DISAPPOINTMENT OVER THERE.

14:08.760 --> 14:10.501
I'M GOING TO WIN
THAT BLUE RIBBON,

14:10.545 --> 14:13.113
WRAP IT AROUND HER NECK,
AND STRANGLE HER WITH IT.

14:13.156 --> 14:14.636
OLIVE,
YOU'RE BAKING WITH HATE.

14:14.679 --> 14:17.552
AH. RICH, BUTTERY,
HIGH-IN-CARBOHYDRATE HATE.

14:17.595 --> 14:18.683
YOU KNOW WHAT
NO ONE TELLS YOU

14:18.727 --> 14:20.250
ABOUT COOKING
WITH THE DARK SIDE?

14:20.294 --> 14:21.599
THE FOOD IS REALLY GOOD.

14:21.643 --> 14:23.123
REVENGE IS A DISH
BEST SERVED COLD.

14:23.166 --> 14:25.865
WE'RE BAKING PIE -- WARM,
DELICIOUS, HAPPY-MAKING PIE.

14:25.908 --> 14:28.302
OKAY, HELP COOK OR GET OUT
OF THE KITCHEN, SHORT-PANTS.

14:28.345 --> 14:29.607
FINE.

14:29.651 --> 14:31.827
AH, THE SWEET SMELL
OF VICTORY!

14:31.871 --> 14:33.176
NOT THIS YEAR,
TURD-MUFFIN.

14:33.220 --> 14:34.612
I'LL SHUT YOUR PIEHOLE
GOOD.

14:34.656 --> 14:36.005
BRING IT, STALE-CAKES!
WE'RE GONNA WIN!

14:36.049 --> 14:38.486
WHO'S "WE," SUCKA?
I'M GONNA WIN.

14:38.529 --> 14:40.792
[ WOMAN SCREAMS ]

14:40.836 --> 14:44.622
[ Southern accent ] MY
HUSBAND, THE COLONEL --
HE'S DEAD!

14:48.931 --> 14:50.367
WHOA!

14:50.411 --> 14:51.455
UH...

14:51.499 --> 14:52.848
[ LIQUID BUBBLING ]
AH.

14:55.242 --> 14:56.243
[ ALL GASP ]

14:56.286 --> 14:58.941
HE'S NOT JUST DEAD.

14:58.985 --> 15:00.464
HE'S EXTRA-CRISPY.

15:06.557 --> 15:10.213
MY HUSBAND, THE COLONEL --
GONE FOREVER.

15:10.257 --> 15:12.085
I'M AFRAID IT LOOKS LIKE
HE COLLAPSED

15:12.128 --> 15:14.478
AND FELL INTO
HIS OWN BOILING OIL.

15:14.522 --> 15:17.568
I ALWAYS KNEW ONE OF
HIS MANY MASSIVE HEART
ATTACKS WOULD DO HIM IN.

15:17.612 --> 15:20.310
AT LEAST THE COLONEL
LEFT THIS WORLD FRYIN'.

15:20.354 --> 15:21.964
SHOULD BE
SOME COMFORT.

15:22.008 --> 15:23.574
THERE'S NO COMFORT
IN KNOWING

15:23.618 --> 15:25.663
THAT THE SECRET RECIPE
WILL DIE ALONG WITH HIM.

15:25.707 --> 15:27.839
IT WAS HIS GREATEST
AND ONLY LEGACY.

15:27.883 --> 15:29.406
SURELY
HE WROTE IT DOWN.

15:29.450 --> 15:30.799
SURELY HE DIDN'T.

15:30.842 --> 15:32.844
MY HUSBAND WAS
A FAT-FRYING SAVANT.

15:32.888 --> 15:35.021
HE KEPT THAT RECIPE
STORED IN HIS HEAD.

15:35.064 --> 15:38.241
IF ONLY I COULD HAVE HIM
BACK FOR ONE MINUTE

15:38.285 --> 15:42.332
[ Sobbing ] TO PRESERVE
HIS LASTING, LOVING MEMORY.

15:42.376 --> 15:43.420
OHH.

15:43.464 --> 15:45.770
OLIVE, UH...
[ CRYING ]

15:45.814 --> 15:47.033
I need your help.

15:47.076 --> 15:48.991
Help me to, uh,
help the widow.

15:49.035 --> 15:50.601
How? Her husband's dead.

15:50.645 --> 15:52.342
What are you gonna do --
haul him back to life

15:52.386 --> 15:54.518
and say, "Colonel,
what's your recipe?"

15:54.562 --> 15:55.998
Uh...

15:56.042 --> 15:57.652
Maybe he left something
behind.

15:57.695 --> 15:59.132
Distract the paramedics
long enough

15:59.175 --> 16:01.917
for me to, uh...
examine the workstation.

16:01.961 --> 16:03.614
Ned...

16:03.658 --> 16:04.659
Uh...

16:08.793 --> 16:10.882
UM...

16:10.926 --> 16:12.449
AAAH! HELP!

16:12.493 --> 16:14.016
MY EYES ARE --
THEY'RE BLEEDING!

16:14.060 --> 16:17.150
[ CRIES ]
HELP! I CAN'T SEE!

16:17.193 --> 16:18.978
[ SCREAMING INDISTINCTLY ]

16:21.676 --> 16:25.027
[ Southern accent ]
I FINALLY KNOW WHAT
MY BIRDS FELT LIKE.

16:25.071 --> 16:26.594
GUESS I'M DEAD, EH?

16:26.637 --> 16:28.552
HEART ATTACK.
NOT A LOT OF TIME.

16:28.596 --> 16:30.554
AND THE WIDOW LIKKIN WANTS TO
PRESERVE YOUR SECRET RECIPE.

16:30.598 --> 16:33.731
GOOD WOMAN, MY BRIDE.
LET'S DO IT.

16:33.775 --> 16:37.300
I GOT ALL 500 HERBS AND SPICES
RIGHT UP HERE.

16:37.344 --> 16:40.738
BETTER PULL UP A CHAIR
AND GRAB YOURSELF A PEN.

16:40.782 --> 16:43.437
THAT SOUNDS LIKE A LONG
TRIP DOWN A LAZY RIVER
WE DON'T HAVE TIME FOR.

16:43.480 --> 16:46.222
NOW,
YOU CAN'T RUSH GOODNESS.

16:46.266 --> 16:48.050
DID YOU SAY
"HEART ATTACK"?

16:48.094 --> 16:49.791
I DID. NOW, SHOULD WE START
WITH THE HERBS OR THE SPICES?

16:49.834 --> 16:51.271
BUSHWAH!

16:51.314 --> 16:54.056
SOME CARPETBAGGING COWARD
SNUCK UP BEHIND,

16:54.100 --> 16:56.276
BATTERED ME
IN MY OWN BATTER,

16:56.319 --> 16:58.452
AND SHOVED ME
INTO BOILING OIL.

16:58.495 --> 17:00.410
THAT WAS MURDER, SON.

17:00.454 --> 17:02.369
REALLY? AND YOU DIDN'T SEE
WHO DID IT?

17:02.412 --> 17:04.327
ATTACKED FROM BEHIND.

17:04.371 --> 17:06.199
THEY WERE STEALTHY,
LIKE A SNAKE...

17:06.242 --> 17:07.200
OR A YANKEE.

17:07.243 --> 17:08.592
OKAY.

17:08.636 --> 17:10.464
LET'S HIT THE HEADLINES
OF THE RECIPE,

17:10.507 --> 17:12.509
AND WITH THE TIME LEFT OVER,
WE CAN CIRCLE BACK
TO THE MURDER.

17:12.553 --> 17:14.511
OH, THIS IS SILLY. ARE YOU
SURE YOU DIDN'T WRITE IT DOWN?

17:14.555 --> 17:16.296
I GOT ONE HANDWRITTEN COPY.

17:16.339 --> 17:18.515
I KEEP IT RIGHT HERE
IN MY --

17:18.559 --> 17:19.603
HERE IN MY --

17:19.647 --> 17:21.475
TARNATION.

17:21.518 --> 17:25.566
THIS FAT-FRYING PROCESS SEEMS
TO HAVE ROBBED ME OF MOBILITY.

17:25.609 --> 17:27.002
THERE'S NOTHING IN THERE.
IMPOSSIBLE.

17:27.046 --> 17:28.612
I'VE KEPT MY RECIPE
RIGHT THERE --

17:28.656 --> 17:31.180
SAME SPOT FOR 30 YEARS.

17:31.224 --> 17:33.617
WHAT SCOUNDREL
STOLE MY SECRET RECIPE?

17:33.661 --> 17:35.793
I'LL FIND OUT, AND I'LL FIND
OUT WHO KILLED YOU, TOO.

17:35.837 --> 17:37.839
BUT NOW
I'M AFRAID TIME IS UP.

17:37.882 --> 17:41.277
I HATE TO GO, BUT AT LEAST
I'M GOING DELICIOUS.

17:42.104 --> 17:44.454
MMM!

17:44.498 --> 17:47.718
Narrator: AND AS THE COLONEL
WENT BACK TO BEING DEAD,

17:47.762 --> 17:51.505
CHUCK FACED THE CONSEQUENCES
OF HER IMPULSIVE DECISION.

17:51.548 --> 17:54.334
THE "BRING DAD BACK" PART,
I DON'T REGRET.

17:54.377 --> 17:55.944
I MEAN,
HOW CAN ANYONE REGRET

17:55.987 --> 17:57.989
BEING REUNITED
WITH SOMEONE THAT THEY LOVE

17:58.033 --> 17:59.513
AND THEY THOUGHT
THEY'D NEVER SEE AGAIN?

17:59.556 --> 18:00.514
POINT TAKEN.

18:00.557 --> 18:02.124
BUT THE BIG PROBLEM --

18:02.168 --> 18:04.170
MAYBE THE BIGGEST PROBLEM,
IN AN OBJECTIVE SENSE --

18:04.213 --> 18:06.172
IS THE DISHONESTY
WITH NED.

18:06.215 --> 18:09.914
THAT AND THE "MAKING
SOMEONE ELSE LESS ALIVE" PART.

18:09.958 --> 18:11.438
"LESS ALIVE."
[ SCOFFS ]

18:11.481 --> 18:13.483
NICE EUPHEMISM...KILLER.

18:13.527 --> 18:15.442
WE WERE AT THE CEMETERY
IN THE DEAD OF NIGHT.

18:15.485 --> 18:17.922
MAYBE THERE WAS NO ONE ELSE
THERE. MAYBE NO ONE ELSE DIED.

18:17.966 --> 18:19.968
YOU THINK THIS IS
A "SOMETIMES" RULE?

18:20.011 --> 18:21.709
NED LETS SOMEBODY LIVE
LONGER THAN A MINUTE

18:21.752 --> 18:23.624
AND SOMEBODY ELSE HAS TO DIE
SOMETIMES?

18:23.667 --> 18:25.539
NO!
IT'S AN "EVERY TIME" RULE!

18:25.582 --> 18:27.193
THERE'S SOME SUCKER OUT THERE
DEAD IN THE LEAVES.

18:27.236 --> 18:28.716
OH, MY GOD.

18:28.759 --> 18:30.761
THEN MAYBE SOME SWEET OLD LADY
WITH INSOMNIA

18:30.805 --> 18:32.676
WHO WAS BRINGING FLOWERS
TO HER HUSBAND'S GRAVE...

18:32.720 --> 18:34.287
I MEAN,
IT COULD HAVE BEEN ANYONE.

18:34.330 --> 18:36.115
I COULD HAVE JUST KILLED
ANY INNOCENT --

18:36.158 --> 18:38.204
EITHER WAY, WE GOT
ANOTHER DEAD BODY TO FIND --

18:38.247 --> 18:40.554
A BODY THAT WAS DEADED BY NED,
ONLY HE DON'T KNOW ABOUT IT

18:40.597 --> 18:41.903
ON ACCOUNT OF
YOU NEVER TOLD HIM,

18:41.946 --> 18:43.252
WHICH IS THE WRONG
I'M CORRECTING.

18:43.296 --> 18:44.993
I KNOW. I KNOW
WHAT I DID WAS WRONG.

18:45.036 --> 18:47.169
BUT I WAS SPURRED TO ACTION
IN THE SPUR OF THE MOMENT,

18:47.213 --> 18:51.391
WHICH LEAVES ME LIVING
IN THE DEEP, DARK WORLD
OF CONSEQUENCE.

18:51.434 --> 18:53.088
BUT IF YOU HELP ME
CLEAN THIS UP,

18:53.132 --> 18:54.829
THEN NED WON'T HAVE TO
LIVE ANYWHERE

18:54.872 --> 18:56.874
BUT THE BRIGHT,
HAPPY WORLD OF PIE,

18:56.918 --> 18:58.920
AND ALL WE'LL HAVE TO
DEAL WITH IS EACH OTHER.

18:58.963 --> 19:00.922
AND YOUR DADDY.
YOU CAN'T KEEP THAT FROM HIM.

19:03.881 --> 19:04.926
OKAY.

19:04.969 --> 19:07.929
WE'LL FIND THE BODY
FIRST.

19:07.972 --> 19:10.801
BUT I'M TELLING YOU,
RIGHT AFTER THAT, YOU GO
STRAIGHT TO PIE BOY.

19:13.021 --> 19:14.849
AH! DON'T BE PECKING ME,
WOMAN!

19:14.892 --> 19:18.200
THAT'S THE PECK OF CAHOOTS,
WHICH WE ARE DEFINITELY NOT
IN.

19:18.244 --> 19:19.723
WELL,
THANK YOU ANYWAY.

19:19.767 --> 19:21.899
[ GRUMBLES ]

19:21.943 --> 19:25.076
Mrs. Likkin:
THE COOK-OFF WILL CONTINUE.

19:25.120 --> 19:27.775
THE COLONEL WOULD HAVE
WANTED IT THAT WAY.

19:27.818 --> 19:30.647
HIS TRAGIC HEART ATTACK
MUST BE HONORED BY US --

19:30.691 --> 19:34.825
HIS SACRED COMMUNITY
OF FELLOW CHEFS.

19:34.869 --> 19:38.916
WHO NOW ALL STAND A MUCH
BETTER CHANCE OF WINNING.

19:38.960 --> 19:39.917
PROCEED.

19:41.267 --> 19:42.659
I KNOW IT'S A TRAGEDY,
OBVIOUSLY,

19:42.703 --> 19:44.139
BUT YOU KNOW
WHAT THEY SAY --

19:44.183 --> 19:45.836
WHEN GOD CLOSES A DOOR,
HE OPENS AN OVEN.

19:45.880 --> 19:47.490
THEY DON'T SAY THAT,
AND IF THEY DO,

19:47.534 --> 19:49.623
THEY DON'T HAVE MUCH
COMPASSION FOR A DEAD COLONEL.

19:49.666 --> 19:51.233
OH, I AM NOT
GONNA LET YOU BAIT ME

19:51.277 --> 19:53.104
TO GET ALL SOFT
AND COMPASSIONY

19:53.148 --> 19:55.672
WHEN WE'RE THIS CLOSE
TO NAILING THIS COMPETITION.

19:55.716 --> 19:57.065
WHAT WOULD YOU SAY
IF I TOLD YOU

19:57.108 --> 19:58.675
I THINK THE COLONEL
WAS MURDERED?

19:58.719 --> 20:00.199
BOO-HOO.
MORE ROOM AT THE TOP.

20:02.201 --> 20:03.941
OH, MY GOD,
YOU'RE NOT KIDDING.

20:03.985 --> 20:05.856
I THINK THE COLONEL HAD A COPY
OF HIS SECRET RECIPE

20:05.900 --> 20:07.684
AND SOMEONE KILLED HIM
FOR IT.

20:07.728 --> 20:09.512
HOW COULD YOU POSSIBLY
KNOW THAT

20:09.556 --> 20:10.948
BY JUST LOOKING
AT HIS DEAD BODY?

20:10.992 --> 20:13.647
I -- I'M AN INVESTIGATOR.

20:13.690 --> 20:15.431
WORKING WITH EMERSON COD
HAS TAUGHT ME THINGS --

20:15.475 --> 20:17.955
DEDUCTIVE AND INDUCTIVE
REASONING, EVIDENCE-GATHERING.

20:17.999 --> 20:21.263
A DEAD BODY CAN SAY A LOT...
TO THE...TRAINED PROFESSIONAL.

20:21.307 --> 20:22.786
MM-HMM.

20:22.830 --> 20:24.397
ANYWAY,
MY EDUCATED HUNCH TELLS ME

20:24.440 --> 20:26.050
THAT THERE'S A MURDER
TO SOLVE.

20:26.094 --> 20:28.966
YOU'VE NEVER SOLVED
A MURDER MYSTERY ALONE BEFORE.

20:29.010 --> 20:30.403
I'M NOT ALONE.

20:35.146 --> 20:36.235
ME?

20:36.278 --> 20:38.889
OH,
I JUST GOT ALL TINGLY.

20:38.933 --> 20:40.630
A-AND NOT JUST
IN THE NETHER REGIONS.

20:40.674 --> 20:43.416
OKAY, HOW DO WE GO ABOUT
THIS -- THIS WHOLE P.I. THING?

20:43.459 --> 20:46.723
DO WE JUST JAM THE GUN
IN THE SUSPECT'S MOUTH
AND SAY "SING, CANARY,

20:46.767 --> 20:50.292
OR I'M GONNA DECORATE THIS
WALLPAPER WITH YOUR GUTS"?

20:50.336 --> 20:51.946
NEITHER.

20:51.989 --> 20:53.295
TECHNICALLY,
I DON'T BELIEVE

20:53.339 --> 20:55.645
YOU CAN BLOW SOMEONE'S GUTS
OUT THEIR MOUTH.

20:55.689 --> 20:56.951
WUSS.

20:56.994 --> 20:59.475
HOLY SMOKES.
OUR OVEN'S SMOKING.

21:02.348 --> 21:03.349
NED.

21:03.392 --> 21:05.307
OH! OH! AAH! AAH!

21:05.351 --> 21:06.482
[ COUGHS ]

21:06.526 --> 21:07.962
[ GRUNTS ]

21:08.005 --> 21:09.572
OH! SABOTAGED!

21:09.616 --> 21:11.574
I BET IT WAS THE BEETLE.

21:11.618 --> 21:14.316
I BET IT WAS
THE COLONEL'S KILLER.

21:14.360 --> 21:16.405
Chuck: I KNOW
THIS DOESN'T TAKE THE STING

21:16.449 --> 21:18.102
OUT OF THE RESPONSIBILITY,
BUT I BROUGHT SOME CASH.

21:18.146 --> 21:20.148
I THOUGHT WHEN
WE FIND THE BODY,

21:20.191 --> 21:21.802
WE'LL TAKE IT
TO THE NEAREST FUNERAL HOME,

21:21.845 --> 21:23.499
WITH THE CASH
AND A NOTE THAT SAYS

21:23.543 --> 21:24.500
"EVERY HUMAN BODY
DESERVES DIGNITY.

21:24.544 --> 21:26.415
PLEASE BURY THIS ONE."

21:26.459 --> 21:28.722
IT'LL BE JUST LIKE
LEAVING A BABY ON A DOORSTEP,

21:28.765 --> 21:31.115
ONLY...
THE TAIL END OF THINGS.

21:31.159 --> 21:34.597
HUH. AND THE POINT OF THIS
WOULD BE, SAY, WHAT?

21:34.641 --> 21:36.207
CLOSURE.

21:36.251 --> 21:37.644
MM-HMM.

21:37.687 --> 21:39.602
WELL, I GOT A FEELING
THE BODY WE FIND

21:39.646 --> 21:41.735
IS GONNA GIVE YOU
ANYTHING BUT CLOSURE.

21:41.778 --> 21:43.345
AND WHERE DO YOU GET
THAT IDEA?

21:43.389 --> 21:45.129
OH, I DIDN'T JUST GET IT.
IT WAS GIVEN TO ME.

21:47.131 --> 21:48.916
BY DWIGHT DIXON.

21:57.446 --> 21:58.404
WHAT WAS DWIGHT DIXON
DOING HERE?

21:58.447 --> 22:00.144
LET ME SHOW YOU SOMETHING.

22:03.670 --> 22:05.019
A RIFLE?!

22:05.062 --> 22:06.455
YEP.

22:06.499 --> 22:07.891
LOOKS LIKE
SWEET OLD DWIGHT

22:07.935 --> 22:09.980
ALREADY HAD HIMSELF
A SHOT LINED UP.

22:10.024 --> 22:12.461
YOUR WEIGHTY CONSCIENCE
MIGHT NOT FEEL SO WEIGHTY

22:12.505 --> 22:13.767
AFTER YOU LOOK
THROUGH HERE.

22:13.810 --> 22:15.464
WHY WOULD HE HAVE
A GUN?

22:19.642 --> 22:22.384
THAT'S MY FATHER'S GRAVE.
HE WAS TRYING TO KILL US?

22:22.428 --> 22:24.517
NOT IF YOU KILLED HIM
FIRST.

22:24.560 --> 22:26.127
WHY WOULD
HE WANT US DEAD?

22:26.170 --> 22:29.217
Narrator: AS IS TRADITIONAL,
THE "WHY" IN THIS CASE

22:29.260 --> 22:32.873
WAS MET WITH AN EQUAL AND
OPPOSITE "BECAUSE."

22:32.916 --> 22:35.179
UPON DISCOVERING
THAT THE POCKET WATCH

22:35.223 --> 22:38.444
HE HAD STOLEN FROM CHUCK
HAD BEEN STOLEN BACK,

22:38.487 --> 22:41.751
DWIGHT SET OUT TO RECLAIM
THE MYSTERIOUS TIME PIECE

22:41.795 --> 22:43.231
ONE LAST TIME.

22:43.274 --> 22:45.276
FOLLOWING CHUCK
TO THE GRAVEYARD,

22:45.320 --> 22:48.410
DWIGHT ASSUMED HER INTENT
WAS TO RETURN THE WATCH

22:48.454 --> 22:51.108
TO THE GRAVE FROM
WHICH IT HAD BEEN STOLEN.

22:51.152 --> 22:53.850
READY TO PULL THE TRIGGER
AND RECLAIM HIS PRIZE,

22:53.894 --> 22:59.160
DWIGHT PAUSED, UNBELIEVING
THE UNBELIEVABLE SIGHT HE SAW.

22:59.203 --> 23:02.250
DWIGHT'S MIND REELED AT THE
SIGHT OF THE PIE MAKER AND
CHUCK

23:02.293 --> 23:05.166
DESECRATING
CHARLES CHARLES' GRAVE.

23:05.209 --> 23:08.474
AND, AS IS TRADITIONAL,
HE DECIDED TO PUT AN END

23:08.517 --> 23:11.259
TO THE THING
HE DID NOT UNDERSTAND.

23:11.302 --> 23:13.870
BUT, AS ALL HIS REELING
AND UNBELIEVING

23:13.914 --> 23:17.178
HAD TAKEN EXACTLY 61
SECONDS...

23:17.221 --> 23:18.353
[ THUNDER CRASHES ]

23:18.397 --> 23:20.224
...NO SHOT WAS EVER FIRED.

23:20.268 --> 23:22.226
Chuck: IF I HADN'T HAVE
KEPT MY DAD ALIVE,

23:22.270 --> 23:23.576
I'D HAVE BEEN MURDERED
TWICE.

23:23.619 --> 23:24.925
YEAH, ONCE WAS ENOUGH.

23:24.968 --> 23:26.796
AND NED -- HE WOULD BE GONE,
TOO.

23:26.840 --> 23:28.929
MY ACCIDENTALLY
KILLING DWIGHT

23:28.972 --> 23:31.714
LIGHTS UP THREE POINTS ON OUR
SIDE OF THE COSMIC SCOREBOARD.

23:31.758 --> 23:33.281
PLUS, YOU SAVE THAT BUNDLE

23:33.324 --> 23:35.457
YOU WOULD HAVE BLOWN
ON BURYING MR. BOOM-BOOM.

23:35.501 --> 23:36.893
BETTER WE BURY HIM
RIGHT HERE.

23:36.937 --> 23:38.417
I GOT A COUPLE SHOVELS
IN THE CAR.

23:38.460 --> 23:40.157
WE'LL GET HIM
UNDER THE DIRT

23:40.201 --> 23:41.724
BEFORE THE "PAY YOUR RESPECTS
AT LUNCH" CROWD SHOWS UP.

23:41.768 --> 23:44.031
BY THE TIME THE GRASS
GROWS BACK OVER THIS PLOT,

23:44.074 --> 23:46.729
IT'LL BE LIKE
NONE OF THIS EVER HAPPENED.

23:46.773 --> 23:49.471
AND I CAN'T WAIT TILL IT'S
LIKE NONE OF THIS EVER
HAPPENED.

23:49.515 --> 23:51.299
BUT IT DID HAPPEN.

23:53.257 --> 23:56.522
SOMEONE SABOTAGED OUR OVEN.
THE FLAME WON'T SHUT OFF.

23:56.565 --> 23:58.567
LET IT BURN -- MAYBE
IT'LL DESTROY THIS BUILDING

23:58.611 --> 24:00.264
AND ALL ITS MEMORIES
OF ALMOST WINNING

24:00.308 --> 24:01.440
WITH THE CLEANSING POWER
OF FLAME.

24:01.483 --> 24:03.746
OLIVE, WE'RE STAYING
IN THE CONTEST.

24:03.790 --> 24:06.183
WE ARE?

24:06.227 --> 24:08.359
WE NEED TO KEEP COMPETING
AS COVER SO WE CAN INVESTIGATE
COLONEL LIKKIN'S MURDER.

24:08.403 --> 24:10.274
WINNING WOULD MAKE
AN EXCELLENT COVER.

24:10.318 --> 24:13.060
WHOEVER KILLED THE COLONEL
IS A RISK-TAKER, DESPERATE --

24:13.103 --> 24:14.453
SAME AS OUR SABOTEUR.

24:14.496 --> 24:16.280
SO FIND THE SABOTEUR,
FIND THE KILLER.

24:16.324 --> 24:17.543
MAYBE WE FIND
OUR INGREDIENTS.

24:17.586 --> 24:18.544
THEY TOOK EVERYTHING WE NEED
TO BAKE PIES.

24:18.587 --> 24:19.588
I'M ON IT.

24:19.632 --> 24:20.676
OLIVE?

24:20.720 --> 24:21.938
VIVIAN? VIVIAN?

24:21.982 --> 24:23.331
VIVIAN,
WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?

24:23.374 --> 24:25.986
OH, HONEY,
HAVE YOU BEEN CRYING?

24:26.029 --> 24:28.597
I STOPPED BY THE PIE HOLE,
BUT IT WAS CLOSED.

24:28.641 --> 24:31.382
AND, YES,
I WAS CRYING.

24:31.426 --> 24:32.862
WHY IS
THE PIE HOLE CLOSED?

24:32.906 --> 24:35.125
IT'S MAN TROUBLE.
I CAN TELL.

24:35.169 --> 24:37.650
I KNEW THAT DWIGHT DIXON
WAS HEARTBREAK WAITING TO POP.

24:37.693 --> 24:39.086
THIS IS LILY'S FAULT.

24:39.129 --> 24:40.827
SHE AIMED A SHOTGUN
AT HIS PRIVATES

24:40.870 --> 24:42.481
AND TOLD HIM
TO STAY AWAY FROM US.

24:42.524 --> 24:45.179
BUT HALF OF US IS ME,
AND I DON'T WANT HIM AWAY.

24:45.222 --> 24:47.137
I WANT HIM CLOSE.

24:47.181 --> 24:48.443
GIVE US A MINUTE.

24:48.487 --> 24:51.751
VIVIAN,
IT'S, UH, GOOD TO SEE YOU.

24:51.794 --> 24:53.013
COME ON.

24:53.056 --> 24:54.318
FORGIVE ME.

24:54.362 --> 24:56.538
I-I'M SO WRAPPED UP
IN MY MAN,

24:56.582 --> 24:58.714
I'M THOUGHTLESSLY
KEEPING YOU FROM YOURS.

24:58.758 --> 25:00.368
WHO? NED?

25:00.411 --> 25:01.630
NO.

25:01.674 --> 25:03.545
NO, WE'RE PARTNERS
IN A CONTEST --

25:03.589 --> 25:05.939
UNROMANTIC PARTNERS,
LIKE A BROTHER AND A SISTER,

25:05.982 --> 25:09.420
LIKE AN ASEXUAL, ANDROGYNOUS
BROTHER AND A SISTER.

25:09.464 --> 25:11.292
[ Laughing ]MYMAN?
HA HA HO!

25:11.335 --> 25:14.164
OH, HEE-HEE.
NO, THAT'S A LAUGH.

25:14.208 --> 25:15.601
[ CHUCKLES ]

25:15.644 --> 25:17.472
WHEN DWIGHT DIDN'T SHOW UP
FOR OUR DATE,

25:17.516 --> 25:19.343
I TRIED TO LAUGH, TOO,

25:19.387 --> 25:23.522
TRIED TO TELL MYSELF MY
FEELINGS FOR HIM WERE SILLY.

25:23.565 --> 25:26.829
BUT LYING TO YOURSELF
ABOUT LOVE NEVER WORKS.

25:28.135 --> 25:29.092
DAMN.

25:29.136 --> 25:30.703
I KNOW.

25:30.746 --> 25:34.881
BUT STILL, I KEEP LYING
AND LOOKING ALL THE SAME.

25:34.924 --> 25:37.100
IF YOU SEE DWIGHT
AT THE PIE HOLE,

25:37.144 --> 25:40.234
WILL YOU TELL HIM
ABOUT THE "LOOKING" PART?

25:40.277 --> 25:41.801
I'D LIKE TO SEE HIM.

25:41.844 --> 25:43.193
I UNDERSTAND.

25:50.026 --> 25:51.941
BOY, DO I UNDERSTAND.

25:51.985 --> 25:54.248
I FOUND SOMETHING.

25:54.291 --> 25:57.033
THE SABOTEUR WHO SABOTAGED
OUR OVEN LEFT BEHIND
ONE STICKY MISTAKE.

25:57.077 --> 26:00.471
OOH, WHAT IS IT?
TOXIC SOOT WITH A DASH OF DNA?

26:00.515 --> 26:02.561
IT'S, UH, SWEET, WOODSY,

26:02.604 --> 26:05.389
LIKE A BERKSHIRE FOREST
ON A CRISP AUTUMN MORNING.

26:05.433 --> 26:07.217
EGH.
CARAMELIZED SUGAR.

26:07.261 --> 26:08.828
MAPLE SYRUP.

26:08.871 --> 26:11.918
ONLY ONE CHEF HERE
USES PURE MAPLE SYRUP.

26:11.961 --> 26:13.920
THE WAFFLE NAZI.
THE WAFFLE NAZI.

26:16.444 --> 26:18.272
[ German accent ]
GOOD, JA? JA.

26:21.057 --> 26:23.582
Narrator: CHUCK HAD SEEN
DEAD BODIES TALK BEFORE,

26:23.625 --> 26:24.626
BUT THIS WAS DIFFERENT.

26:24.670 --> 26:26.323
THIS WAS JUST HER GUILTY MIND

26:26.367 --> 26:28.761
GIVING RISE
TO HER GUILTY FEELINGS.

26:28.804 --> 26:30.153
Chuck:
YOU'RE JUST MY GUILTY MIND

26:30.197 --> 26:32.808
GIVING RISE
TO MY GUILTY FEELINGS.

26:32.852 --> 26:36.420
DOESN'T CHANGE THE FACT THAT
YOU HAVE ROYALLY SCREWED UP.

26:36.464 --> 26:38.118
FINE.
YOU TALK, I'LL SHOVEL.

26:38.161 --> 26:41.469
WAS IT WORTH IT?
SURE, FINE, I'M A BAD MAN.

26:41.512 --> 26:44.037
YOU SAVED THREE GOOD PEOPLE
BY PUTTING ME DOWN --

26:44.080 --> 26:46.517
A THREE-FOR-ONE SALE
ON THE GRANDEST SCALE.

26:46.561 --> 26:49.172
ANYTIME
WITH THOSE SHOVELS!

26:49.216 --> 26:50.870
WHAT WOULD YOU HAVE DONE?

26:50.913 --> 26:53.437
SAME THING, PROBABLY.
I'D HAVE KILLED YOU, TOO.

26:53.481 --> 26:54.874
BUT HERE'S THE DIFFERENCE.

26:54.917 --> 26:56.179
EMERSON!

26:56.223 --> 26:58.486
I WOULD HAVE TOLD NED
BY NOW.

26:58.529 --> 26:59.618
SHUT UP!

26:59.661 --> 27:00.793
WHO YOU TALKING TO?

27:00.836 --> 27:02.969
SHUT UP!

27:03.012 --> 27:04.666
NOTHING. NO ONE.

27:04.710 --> 27:06.625
I DON'T NEED TO TALK
TO ANYONE ABOUT ANYTHING,

27:06.668 --> 27:07.669
'CAUSE MY CONSCIENCE
IS CLEAR.

27:07.713 --> 27:10.106
GOOD.
THEN GRAB A SHOVEL.

27:10.150 --> 27:11.891
NED WILL NEVER
FORGIVE YOU.

27:14.545 --> 27:16.373
[ GRUNTING ]

27:21.161 --> 27:24.686
This is an incredible
violation of the
P.C.C.F.C.O. rule

27:24.730 --> 27:27.036
that says no chef is allowed
in another chef's kitchen.

27:27.080 --> 27:28.603
It's immediate
disqualification.

27:28.647 --> 27:30.083
Concentrate
on the killer.

27:30.126 --> 27:32.433
That Waffle Nazi
is likely our saboteur.

27:32.476 --> 27:33.869
Find the saboteur,
find the killer.

27:33.913 --> 27:34.870
Go, go, go, go.

27:34.914 --> 27:36.742
Me?
Go.

27:36.785 --> 27:39.788
Man: ATTENTION, CONTESTANTS.
THIS IS YOUR
20-MINUTE WARNING.

27:42.008 --> 27:43.879
Any evidence linking Waffle
Nazi to Colonel Likkin

27:43.923 --> 27:45.707
would wrap this case up
in brown paper

27:45.751 --> 27:48.754
and tie it up
with a strong, sturdy twine.

27:48.797 --> 27:50.581
Yeah. Oh, yeah.

27:50.625 --> 27:52.192
Hey, you know what I love
about Vivian?

27:52.235 --> 27:53.628
Her imagination.

27:53.672 --> 27:55.586
She thought you and I
were a couple now.

27:55.630 --> 27:56.587
[ CHUCKLES ]

27:56.631 --> 27:57.893
IT'S CRAZY.

27:57.937 --> 27:59.982
IT'S LIKE IMAGINING US
AS HOBBITS...

28:00.026 --> 28:02.681
OR ON JET PACKS...

28:02.724 --> 28:04.030
OR HOBBITS
ON JET PACKS.

28:04.073 --> 28:05.422
[ CHUCKLES ]

28:05.466 --> 28:09.862
ISN'T THE IDEA
OF US ROMANTICALLY ENTWINED

28:09.905 --> 28:11.733
A PANIC, A SCREAM,

28:11.777 --> 28:14.518
A FOUR-HOUR HEART ATTACK
OF COMPLETE IMPOSSIBILITY?

28:14.562 --> 28:15.519
IT ALL MAKES SENSE.

28:17.260 --> 28:18.392
IT DOES?

28:18.435 --> 28:19.959
THIS BATTER'S
BETTER THAN BATTER.

28:20.002 --> 28:21.569
IT'S THE EVIDENCE WE NEED
TO WRAP UP THIS CASE.

28:21.612 --> 28:22.570
HURRAY.

28:23.571 --> 28:24.703
WHAT IS IT?

28:26.443 --> 28:27.401
MMM!

28:27.444 --> 28:28.794
DELICIOUS!

28:28.837 --> 28:30.578
SAVORY, NOT SWEET.

28:30.621 --> 28:32.754
BURSTING WITH
WHAT'S GOT TO BE LIKE...

28:32.798 --> 28:34.625
500 HERBS AND SPICES.

28:34.669 --> 28:35.931
IT'S THE COLONEL'S
SECRET RECIPE.

28:39.195 --> 28:41.110
AND THE KILLER
ON A PLATE.

28:41.154 --> 28:43.199
SIR,
I ACCUSE YOU OF --

28:43.243 --> 28:44.418
SABOTAGE!

28:44.461 --> 28:46.550
YOU HAVE SABOTAGED
MEIN IRONS!

28:46.594 --> 28:48.117
W-WE DIDN'T DO THAT.

28:48.161 --> 28:50.119
DON'T CRY,
MEIN HERR.

28:50.163 --> 28:52.034
LOOK --
IT'S JUSTICE O'CLOCK.

28:52.078 --> 28:53.253
I'M TELLING.

28:53.296 --> 28:54.341
[ GASPS ]

28:58.606 --> 29:00.695
WELL, PIE HOLERS,
IT LOOKS AS IF

29:00.739 --> 29:03.611
YOU ARE SOON TO BE ELIMINATED
FROM ZE COMPETITION.

29:03.654 --> 29:05.961
WE'RE KICKING YOU OUT
BEFORE YOU BAKED YOURSELF OUT.

29:06.005 --> 29:08.485
WHEN LEO BURNS TOOTLES UP
ON HIS SCOOTER

29:08.529 --> 29:10.487
AND SEES HOW MANY RULES
YOU HAVE BROKEN,

29:10.531 --> 29:13.186
YOUR DREAMS OF COMFORT-FOOD
GLORY ARE KAPUT.

29:13.229 --> 29:15.275
YOU SAW OUR OVEN.
WE WERE SABOTAGED, TOO.

29:15.318 --> 29:17.364
LIARS ROAST IN HELL.

29:17.407 --> 29:18.495
JUST SAYIN'.

29:18.539 --> 29:19.540
WE'RE NOT
THE SABOTEURS.

29:19.583 --> 29:21.629
OH, JA, JA.

29:21.672 --> 29:23.500
MEIN WAFFLE CORD
LEAPED INTO YOUR ARMS

29:23.544 --> 29:26.460
LIKE A PUPPY WANTING LOVE
AND THEN CUT ITSELF IN TWO.

29:26.503 --> 29:28.201
WHEN WE PRESENT
THE EVIDENCE WE GOT,

29:28.244 --> 29:30.943
YOU CAN KISS THE COOK-OFF
AUF WIEDERSEHEN.

29:30.986 --> 29:32.553
HMM?

29:32.596 --> 29:34.294
IT'S "GOODBYE"
IN GERMAN.

29:34.337 --> 29:36.165
I DO NOT SPEAK
A WORD OF GERMAN.

29:36.209 --> 29:39.908
I SPEAK ENGLISH
MIT A GERMAN ACCENT.

29:39.952 --> 29:42.215
[ American accent ]
PAGEANTRY.

29:42.258 --> 29:45.958
WE FOUND THIS BATCH
OF THE COLONEL'S SECRET
RECIPE IN YOUR KITCHEN.

29:46.001 --> 29:48.003
THAT'S A BIG BOWL
OF MOTIVE, FRITZ.

29:48.047 --> 29:49.352
ARE YOU SUGGESTING MURDER?

29:49.396 --> 29:50.963
[ SCOFFS ] RIDICULOUS.

29:51.006 --> 29:54.053
HERR LIKKIN AND I WERE SOON
TO BECOME BUSINESS PARTNERS.

29:54.096 --> 29:55.663
CHICKEN AND WAFFLES?

29:55.706 --> 29:57.186
WOULD HAVE CAUGHT POPEYES
WITH THEIR PANTS DOWN.

29:57.230 --> 29:58.231
[ WHIRRING ]

29:58.274 --> 30:00.102
[ TIRES SCREECH ]

30:00.146 --> 30:03.149
WHAT IN THE NAME OF JULIA
CHILD ARE YOU PEOPLE DOING?

30:03.192 --> 30:05.847
I CAN'T COUNT THE NUMBER
OF RULES VIOLATIONS GOING ON.

30:05.891 --> 30:07.806
I'M SO DISAPPOINTED.

30:07.849 --> 30:10.069
THERE MAY BE THE APPEARANCE
OF RULES BEING BENT
OR BROKEN COMPLETELY,

30:10.112 --> 30:12.375
BUT THERE'S A BIGGER PICTURE
YOU NEED TO SEE.

30:12.419 --> 30:14.247
I JUST HAVEN'T FINISHED
PAINTING IT YET.

30:14.290 --> 30:15.857
YEAH, WE'RE NOT
THE SABOTEURS.

30:15.901 --> 30:17.163
POPPYCOCK.

30:17.206 --> 30:19.034
THE PIE HOLE
IS DISQUALIFIED.

30:19.078 --> 30:20.035
[ GASPS ]

30:26.912 --> 30:28.783
ALL RIGHT,
THAT OUGHT TO DO IT.

30:28.827 --> 30:30.698
LET'S GET OUT OF HERE.
NO, WAIT.

30:30.741 --> 30:33.483
WE NEED A PRIEST OR A RABBI
OR SOMEBODY TO SAY SOMETHING.

30:33.527 --> 30:34.920
WHAT?!

30:34.963 --> 30:36.530
DWIGHT MIGHT NOT HAVE BEEN
THE NICEST MAN,

30:36.573 --> 30:39.315
BUT EVERYBODY DESERVES
A BURIAL WITH DIGNITY.

30:39.359 --> 30:42.144
FINE. I GOT BUTTLOADS
OF DIGNITY TO SPRINKLE
ON THE GROUND.

30:42.188 --> 30:43.493
COME ON. GET HOLY.

30:43.537 --> 30:44.973
THANK YOU.

30:45.017 --> 30:46.366
HERE LIES DWIGHT.
HERE LIES HIS GUN.

30:46.409 --> 30:47.715
HE WAS BAD.
NOW HE'S DONE.

30:47.758 --> 30:49.630
LET'S GO.

30:49.673 --> 30:52.415
ALL THIS AND I STILL
HAVE TO DEAL WITH MY MOTHER?

30:52.459 --> 30:54.722
DON'T YOU MEAN "FATHER"?

30:54.765 --> 30:56.811
[ CAT SCREECHES ]

30:56.855 --> 30:59.205
LILY.
[ CHUCKLES ]

30:59.248 --> 31:00.510
DELIGHTED.

31:00.554 --> 31:03.339
CAN THE CRAP
AND SELL IT TO THE TOURISTS.

31:03.383 --> 31:04.558
WHAT ARE YOU DOING
HERE, COD?

31:04.601 --> 31:05.994
WHAT IN THE HELL
ARE YOU DOING HERE?

31:06.038 --> 31:09.519
WAITING
FOR DWIGHT DIXON.

31:09.563 --> 31:12.044
WELL, UH,
HE MAY, UH, DISAPPOINT.

31:12.087 --> 31:13.306
MEN DO THAT.

31:13.349 --> 31:15.525
WHAT'S WITH THE SHOTGUN?

31:15.569 --> 31:16.918
MILITARY SALUTE.

31:16.962 --> 31:18.572
FOR DWIGHT DIXON?

31:18.615 --> 31:20.530
FOR CHARLES.

31:20.574 --> 31:24.143
BUT IF I HAPPEN TO MISS
AND BLOW DWIGHT'S HEAD OFF,

31:24.186 --> 31:25.579
PURELY BY ACCIDENT,

31:25.622 --> 31:27.407
WELL, THAT'S SOMETHING

31:27.450 --> 31:29.713
MY LAWYERS CAN PRETTY MUCH
SORT OUT LATER.

31:29.757 --> 31:31.759
WELL, UH,
SO LOVELY CATCHING UP.

31:37.983 --> 31:40.028
WELL,
THAT'S EVERYTHING.

31:40.072 --> 31:41.900
BUT THERE'S NO TRUNK
BIG ENOUGH

31:41.943 --> 31:44.685
TO CARRY HOME MY BUSTED DREAMS
OF BLUE-RIBBON VICTORY.

31:44.728 --> 31:46.252
BACK TO
THE PIE HOLE.

31:46.295 --> 31:48.167
WHICH IS EMPTY,
WHICH IS STRANGE,

31:48.210 --> 31:50.169
BECAUSE
CHUCK SHOULD BE THERE.

31:50.212 --> 31:51.735
[ SIGHS ]

31:51.779 --> 31:53.607
THE COLONEL'S
CHICKEN BOOTH.

31:53.650 --> 31:57.306
AN EMPTY NEST
CHOCK-FULL OF CLUES.

31:57.350 --> 31:59.178
A REALLY BOLD
DETECTIVE TEAM

31:59.221 --> 32:01.049
WOULD SNEAK OVER
FOR ONE LAST BIT OF RECON

32:01.093 --> 32:02.877
BEFORE PACKING UP
THEIR POTS AND PANS FOR GOOD.

32:09.188 --> 32:12.452
Woman: REMEMBER,
BAKERS' HATS AND HAIRNETS

32:12.495 --> 32:14.976
MUST BE WORN AT ALL TIMES.

32:15.020 --> 32:16.412
[ EXHALES
HEAVILY ]

32:16.456 --> 32:18.632
MEMORIZE THE SCENE --
EVERY DETAIL --

32:18.675 --> 32:19.981
THE PRINTS IN THE BATTER,
THE FOOTPRINTS,

32:20.025 --> 32:21.200
THE GURNEY TRACKS.

32:21.243 --> 32:22.418
WHAT'S THAT?

32:22.462 --> 32:24.072
OH, SPRINKLES.

32:24.116 --> 32:25.247
I LOVE SPRINKLES.

32:25.291 --> 32:26.770
YOU LOVE CLUES.

32:26.814 --> 32:30.035
TWO GREAT TASTES
THAT TASTE GREAT TOGETHER.

32:30.078 --> 32:31.079
[ SPITS ]

32:31.123 --> 32:32.646
UGH!

32:32.689 --> 32:34.822
PAINTED PLASTIC --
CHEAP JEWELRY.

32:34.865 --> 32:36.867
LEFT HERE BEFORE
THE COLONEL WAS KILLED.

32:36.911 --> 32:39.000
WHICH MEANS
THEY BELONG TO THE KILLER.

32:39.044 --> 32:42.699
ATTENTION, CONTESTANTS,
THIS IS YOUR 10-MINUTE
WARNING.

32:42.743 --> 32:44.049
[ CLANG ]
UGH!

32:44.092 --> 32:45.224
[ CLANG ]
AAH!

32:45.267 --> 32:47.008
[ THUD ]

32:49.576 --> 32:50.664
[ HUMS ]

32:50.707 --> 32:52.579
LA-DA-DA DI DI DI.

32:55.582 --> 32:57.018
THE MOST IMPORTANT THING

32:57.062 --> 32:58.715
IS TO KEEP OUR WITS ABOUT US
AND OUR NERVES STEADY.

32:58.759 --> 33:00.456
THERE'S NO GOOD
IN FREAKING OUT,

33:00.500 --> 33:02.545
SO DON'T GO CRAZY AND START --
I DON'T KNOW -- KISSING ME

33:02.589 --> 33:03.938
OR SOMETHING RIDICULOUS
LIKE THAT.

33:03.982 --> 33:05.679
JUST BECAUSE
WE'RE LOCKED IN A TRUNK,

33:05.722 --> 33:07.289
WE COULD DIE
AT ANY MINUTE...

33:07.333 --> 33:09.030
WHAT ARE YOU --
[ THUMPING ]

33:09.074 --> 33:10.075
HEY!

33:10.118 --> 33:11.119
[ GRUNTS ]

33:11.163 --> 33:12.686
CLEAN THOUGHTS, CHUM.

33:12.729 --> 33:13.730
UH? UH?

33:13.774 --> 33:14.775
[ THUMP ]
OH!

33:14.818 --> 33:15.863
[ MARIANNE SCREAMS ]

33:15.906 --> 33:16.864
WHEW!

33:16.907 --> 33:18.126
[ CHUCKLES ]

33:18.170 --> 33:20.215
HA!
OH!

33:20.259 --> 33:22.913
DON'T MAKE ME WHIP UP
ANOTHER BATCH OF BEAT-DOWN.

33:22.957 --> 33:24.741
Olive: LOOK --
CHEAP PLASTIC EARRINGS.

33:24.785 --> 33:26.656
YOU'RE THE KILLER!

33:26.700 --> 33:28.658
YOU'RE THE KILLER.
YOU DEEP-FAT-FRIED THE
COLONEL.

33:28.702 --> 33:30.921
SUPPOSE YOU WERE GONNA
BAKE ME IN MY OWN OVEN.

33:30.965 --> 33:32.140
NOBODY'S BAKING ANYBODY.

33:32.184 --> 33:33.794
IF YOU WEREN'T HERE
TO KILL THE COLONEL,

33:33.837 --> 33:35.535
WHAT WERE YOU DOING HERE
RIGHT BEFORE HE GOT KILLED?

33:35.578 --> 33:38.059
I THOUGHT THE COLONEL DIED
OF A HEART ATTACK.

33:38.103 --> 33:41.236
I ONLY SNUCK IN HERE
TO TRY TO...

33:41.280 --> 33:42.411
YOU'RE THE SABOTEUR.

33:42.455 --> 33:43.891
BUT NOT THE KILLER.

33:43.934 --> 33:46.850
SABOTAGE IS A
DISQUALIFYING OFFENSE. HA!

33:46.894 --> 33:49.723
IN THE GOOD LORD'S GOOD NAME,
HAVE MERCY.

33:49.766 --> 33:51.246
I NEED THAT
BLUE-RIBBON PRIZE

33:51.290 --> 33:54.423
IF MUFFIN BUFFALO
IS TO ROAM AGAIN.

33:54.467 --> 33:57.992
YOU SEE BEFORE YOU
A DESPERATE WOMAN,

33:58.036 --> 33:59.559
NOT A KILLER.

33:59.602 --> 34:01.474
MARIANNE MARIE BEETLE!

34:01.517 --> 34:02.953
YOU CAN'T BE IN HERE.

34:02.997 --> 34:04.738
DISQUALIFIED.

34:04.781 --> 34:07.654
PIE HOLERS, YOU CAN'T BE IN
HERE AT ALL --
BANNED FOR LIFE.

34:07.697 --> 34:09.395
WHICH REMINDS ME --
I FORGOT TO REPORT

34:09.438 --> 34:10.700
YOUR DISQUALIFICATION
TO THE JUDGES,

34:10.744 --> 34:12.398
WHICH I'M GOING TO DO
RIGHT NOW.

34:12.441 --> 34:13.442
YOU'RE THE KILLER.

34:15.357 --> 34:16.489
HEY.

34:16.532 --> 34:18.665
ME? LOOK AT ME?

34:18.708 --> 34:20.449
I RIDE A SCOOTER.

34:20.493 --> 34:22.364
WHAT KIND OF KILLER
COULD I POSSIBLY BE?

34:22.408 --> 34:24.105
THE KIND
THAT LEAVES TRACKS.

34:24.149 --> 34:25.672
THOSE ARE GURNEY TRACKS

34:25.715 --> 34:28.283
FROM WHERE THE PARAMEDICS
WHEELED AWAY COLONEL LIKKIN.

34:28.327 --> 34:30.329
THOSE FLATTENED TREADS
THAT GO FROM THE BATTER

34:30.372 --> 34:32.244
BACK TO THE DEEP FRYER
ARE KILLER TRACKS --

34:33.854 --> 34:34.811
YOURS.

34:34.855 --> 34:36.161
[ MARIANNE GASPS ]

34:36.204 --> 34:38.685
THOSE ARE HOT-OIL BURNS
ON YOUR HANDS.

34:38.728 --> 34:41.731
DID THE COLONEL SPATTER
WHEN YOU DEEP-FAT-FRIED HIM,

34:41.775 --> 34:44.125
YOU SICK SON OF A BITCH?!

34:44.169 --> 34:46.693
[ SCOFFS ]
PIXIE DUST AND LEMONADE!

34:46.736 --> 34:48.216
YOU HAVE NO PROOF.

34:48.260 --> 34:51.959
THAT STORY WILL NEVER
HOLD UP IN COURT.

34:52.002 --> 34:53.656
THIS WILL.

34:53.700 --> 34:56.224
OH, THE COLONEL'S
SECRET RECIPE.

34:56.268 --> 34:58.139
YOU'RE BUSTED,
TUBBY.

34:58.183 --> 34:59.662
[ GROANS ]

34:59.706 --> 35:01.490
Narrator:
THE FACTS WERE THESE --

35:01.534 --> 35:04.667
ONE YEAR AGO, LEO BURNS
WAS A SLENDER AND HAPPY

35:04.711 --> 35:06.495
BUT SLIGHTLY LONELY MAN.

35:06.539 --> 35:09.107
ONE DAY, HE CHOSE
TO DROWN HIS SORROWS

35:09.150 --> 35:13.241
IN A BUCKET OF
COLONEL LIKKIN'S
SOUTHERN-FRIED CHICKEN...

35:13.285 --> 35:15.069
WHICH LED TO ANOTHER...

35:15.113 --> 35:16.549
AND ANOTHER.

35:16.592 --> 35:18.855
AND SOON,
THE COLONEL'S UNIQUE BLEND

35:18.899 --> 35:24.165
OF 500 HERBS AND SPICES
WERE ALL LEO COULD EAT.

35:24.209 --> 35:26.472
DIABETES, OBESITY,
AND NIGHT BLINDNESS

35:26.515 --> 35:28.256
WERE ALL QUICK TO FOLLOW

35:28.300 --> 35:33.000
THE COATED VOLUMES OF WINGS,
BREASTS, AND THIGHS LEO ATE.

35:33.043 --> 35:35.524
HAVING LOST HIMSELF TO LIKKIN,

35:35.568 --> 35:40.007
LEO VOWED TO DESTROY THE
COLONEL AND HIS
PRECIOUS RECIPE.

35:40.050 --> 35:44.533
LEO VOLUNTEERED AS THIS YEAR'S
COMFORT-FOOD COORDINATOR,

35:44.577 --> 35:47.710
WAITING FOR THE COLONEL
TO MAKE HIS ANNUAL APPEARANCE,

35:47.754 --> 35:50.626
WHICH WOULD BECOME
HIS FINAL APPEARANCE.

35:50.670 --> 35:54.021
BUT LEO COULD NOT BRING
HIMSELF TO DESTROY
THE SECRET RECIPE

35:54.064 --> 35:56.763
THAT ROBBED HIM OF HIS LIFE.

35:56.806 --> 35:59.026
AND THAT WAS HIS UNDOING.

35:59.069 --> 36:01.202
[ GRUNTING ]

36:01.246 --> 36:03.509
Man: ATTENTION,
COOK-OFF CONTESTANTS.

36:03.552 --> 36:06.294
ALL ENTRIES MUST BE
ON THE JUDGES' TABLE

36:06.338 --> 36:10.559
IN 30 SECONDS --
30 SECONDS.

36:10.603 --> 36:12.213
LEO NEVER REPORTED
OUR DISQUALIFICATION.

36:12.257 --> 36:13.649
WHAT CAN WE DO
IN 30 SECONDS?

36:13.693 --> 36:15.216
WE HAVE NOTHING,
AND OUR OVEN IS BROKEN.

36:15.260 --> 36:17.479
REVENGE IS A DISH
BEST SERVED COLD.

36:17.523 --> 36:20.308
WHICH IS WHY I BROUGHT
ONE OF YOUR KILLER
ICEBOX LEMON PIES,

36:20.352 --> 36:22.702
STORED IT IN OUR FRIDGE,
AND CALLED IT "PLAN 'B.'"

36:22.745 --> 36:25.052
DON'T MEAN SQUAT IF IT ISN'T
ON THE JUDGES' TABLE IN...

36:25.095 --> 36:28.664
20 SECONDS --
20 SECONDS.

36:38.196 --> 36:39.197
AAH!

36:39.240 --> 36:40.328
[ CLOCK TICKING ]

36:43.157 --> 36:45.072
[ PANTING ]

36:53.559 --> 36:56.344
[ Distorted ]
AAH! AAAH!

36:56.388 --> 36:58.259
MOVE IT!

36:58.303 --> 36:59.347
Olive: AAH!

36:59.391 --> 37:00.609
[ CHEERS AND APPLAUSE ]

37:08.748 --> 37:09.879
[ TIRES SCREECHING ]

37:12.099 --> 37:13.143
[ BUZZER ]

37:13.187 --> 37:14.144
[ CROWD CHEERING ]

37:22.327 --> 37:24.590
THE COLONEL
WOULD BE SO PROUD.

37:24.633 --> 37:26.069
NOW THAT I HAVE
THE RECIPE,

37:26.113 --> 37:27.593
THAT NICE DOUGHNUT MAN
AND I

37:27.636 --> 37:29.421
ARE GONNA GO
INTO BUSINESS TOGETHER.

37:29.464 --> 37:31.292
"FINGER LIKKIN
DOUGHNUT HOLES."

37:31.336 --> 37:32.467
SOUNDS DELICIOUS...

37:32.511 --> 37:34.426
AND FILTHY.

37:34.469 --> 37:37.124
AMERICA'S FAVORITE --
YOU'LL MAKE A FORTUNE.

37:37.167 --> 37:39.561
Shh! Shh! Shh!

37:39.605 --> 37:42.216
THE BLUE-RIBBON
FIRST PRIZE

37:42.260 --> 37:45.611
IN THIS YEAR'S
ANNUAL COMFORT FOOD COOK-OFF

37:45.654 --> 37:47.700
GOES TO...

37:47.743 --> 37:49.223
THE PIE HOLE!

37:49.267 --> 37:50.833
[ CHEERS AND APPLAUSE ]

38:11.332 --> 38:13.291
[ APPLAUSE FADES ]

38:13.334 --> 38:14.770
[ "ETERNAL FLAME" PLAYS ]

38:19.819 --> 38:22.300
Olive:
♪ CLOSE YOUR EYES

38:22.343 --> 38:25.825
♪ GIVE ME YOUR HAND, DARLING

38:25.868 --> 38:30.046
♪ DO YOU FEEL
MY HEART BEATING? ♪

38:30.090 --> 38:32.745
♪ DO YOU UNDERSTAND?

38:32.788 --> 38:36.052
♪ DO YOU FEEL THE SAME?

38:36.096 --> 38:40.579
♪ OR AM I ONLY DREAMING?

38:40.622 --> 38:43.756
♪ OR IS THIS BURNING

38:43.799 --> 38:47.673
♪ AN ETERNAL FLAME?

38:47.716 --> 38:49.239
♪ SAY MY NAME

38:49.283 --> 38:50.458
Ned: IT'S CHUCK.

38:50.502 --> 38:52.460
IT'S...OLIVE.

38:52.504 --> 38:54.027
NO, IT'S CHUCK.
I DON'T KNOW WHERE SHE IS.

38:54.070 --> 38:55.681
SHE SAID SHE'D BE
AT THE PIE HOLE ALL DAY,

38:55.724 --> 38:57.073
AND IF SHE WAS THERE
ALL DAY,

38:57.117 --> 38:58.379
SHE WOULD HAVE ANSWERED
HER PHONE.

38:58.423 --> 39:00.816
MAYBE SHE'S STEPPING OUT --
STEPPED OUT.

39:00.860 --> 39:02.165
I DON'T KNOW
WHERE SHE IS.

39:02.209 --> 39:03.558
VIVIAN DOESN'T KNOW
WHERE DWIGHT IS.

39:03.602 --> 39:04.951
WHAT IF DWIGHT
LEAVING CHUCK'S OBITUARY

39:04.994 --> 39:07.214
WAS MORE
THAN AN INSURANCE POLICY?

39:07.257 --> 39:09.738
DO YOU MIND
IF I GO LOOK FOR HER?

39:09.782 --> 39:10.870
NO, I DON'T MIND.

39:13.046 --> 39:15.222
SORRY TO LEAVE YOU
WITH THE MESS.

39:15.265 --> 39:16.354
I'M USED TO THE MESS.

39:19.792 --> 39:22.403
♪ SUN SHINES THROUGH
THE RAIN ♪

39:22.447 --> 39:25.406
♪ A WHOLE LIFE SO LONELY

39:25.450 --> 39:29.628
♪ AND THEN YOU COME
AND EASE THE PAIN ♪

39:29.671 --> 39:36.286
♪ I DON'T WANT
TO LOSE THIS FEELING ♪

39:36.330 --> 39:38.114
♪ SAY MY NAME

39:38.158 --> 39:39.115
OLIVE?

39:39.159 --> 39:40.203
HUH?

39:40.247 --> 39:43.250
CONGRATULATIONS,
PARTNER.

39:43.293 --> 39:45.034
CONGRATULATIONS TO YOU, TOO,
PARTNER.

39:48.386 --> 39:52.651
♪ DO YOU FEEL
MY HEART BEATING? ♪

39:52.694 --> 39:55.218
♪ DO YOU UNDERSTAND?

39:55.262 --> 39:58.439
♪ DO YOU FEEL THE SAME?

39:58.483 --> 40:03.096
♪ OR AM I ONLY DREAMING?

40:03.139 --> 40:06.534
♪ OR IS THIS BURNING

40:06.578 --> 40:11.060
♪ AN ETERNAL...

40:11.104 --> 40:13.933
♪ FLA-A-A-A-ME?

40:22.115 --> 40:23.159
[ GASPS ] NED.

40:23.203 --> 40:24.334
HELLO, VIVIAN.

40:24.378 --> 40:25.727
LILY.

40:25.771 --> 40:27.468
I WAS IN THE NEIGHBORHOOD --
PASSING BY, REALLY,

40:27.512 --> 40:29.470
WHEN I WONDERED
IF YOU MIGHT LIKE SOME PIE...

40:29.514 --> 40:31.037
WHICH I FORGOT TO BRING.

40:31.080 --> 40:33.518
BUT WHILE I'M HERE,
I WAS ALSO WONDERING

40:33.561 --> 40:35.258
IF YOU KNEW WHERE I MIGHT FIND
DWIGHT DIXON.

40:35.302 --> 40:37.826
NINTH CIRCLE OF HELL,
IF THERE'S ANY JUSTICE.

40:37.870 --> 40:39.306
LILY, STOP.

40:39.349 --> 40:41.482
WE DON'T KNOW
WHERE DWIGHT IS.

40:41.526 --> 40:43.136
AND HOW COULD YOU FORGET
A THING LIKE PIE?

40:43.179 --> 40:45.486
I FIND THAT CURIOUS.
IT COMES IN A BOX, YOU KNOW.

40:45.530 --> 40:48.446
SAY, YOU GOT A SQUATTER
IN YOUR OLD DIGS OVER THERE?

40:48.489 --> 40:49.534
HMM?

40:53.363 --> 40:54.452
I'LL FIND OUT.

41:00.588 --> 41:03.852
Narrator:
THE PIE MAKER BRACED HIMSELF
TO FIND CHUCK HELD HOSTAGE

41:03.896 --> 41:06.812
BY THE DEADLY, DESPERATE
DWIGHT DIXON.

41:06.855 --> 41:10.511
CHUCK?

41:10.555 --> 41:11.860
I WAS WORRIED.
I THOUGHT --

41:11.904 --> 41:12.992
Charles: CHARLOTTE.

41:13.035 --> 41:14.994
IT'S OKAY, DAD.

41:15.037 --> 41:16.038
"DAD"?

41:18.345 --> 41:20.086
I WAS GONNA TELL YOU.
